Title: Analyzing long win streaks in online chess
Description: TL;DR: In-depth analysis of recent data suggests a high likelihood of Hikaru Nakamura achieving a 55-game winning streak in online blitz, based on thousands of his games played this year (and even more likely given that Hikaru just crossed 35,000 blitz games mark on Chess.com alone). Similarly, longest streaks by Magnus Carlsen (32 wins), Nihal Sarin (22 wins), and Daniel Naroditsky (33 wins) align with statistical expectations. The occurrence of both short (10+ wins) and long (15+ wins) streaks among these elite players is also found to be probable and not out of the ordinary.
